  "biography_html": "<div class=\"research-section\">\n<p class=\"research-text\">No biographical information exists for an author named Assembly of the Birds, as this is the title of a work, not a personal name. The poem dates from the Late Antique or early Byzantine period, between the 4th and 10th centuries CE, but its creator remains anonymous.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">The sole known work is the poem Assembly of the Birds, composed in Byzantine Greek verse. Its state of preservation is not recorded.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">The work’s significance is undefined due to a lack of surviving detail. Its title implies a potential connection to allegorical or fable traditions, but no content, context, or influence is attested in the extant source record.</p>\n</div>",
